      "writtenOn": "2020-11-12T21:55:25Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I\u0027m not a fan of this solution, it mixes API intended for bots with API for end clients.\n\nSince we\u0027ll need server side changed either way, can we instead change UpdateBuild API slightly to say: \"UpdateBuild can update only running builds. Returns FailedPrecondition error otherwise\"?\n\nThen in bbagent just recognized FailedPrecondition before first successful UpdateBuild as \"probably is still SCHEDULER\".",
      "revId": "93b90e3f224835ca4e5efcc18bc10edd0fd4a943",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": false,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "a5228a10_0c841c08",
        "filename": "/PATCHSET_LEVEL",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 0,
      "author": {
        "id": 1381059
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-11-13T00:50:19Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Make sense. I don\u0027t know the discrepancy between BB APIs for different types of callers.\n\nI can certainly change BB to return FailedPrecondtion as it sounds like a better status code to return than InvalidArgument.\n\nHowever, the other thing this change need to solve is that what if there\u0027s a delay in BB to move the status from SCHEDULED to STARTED and the build execute too quick that it finishes before it has seen the first successful UpdateBuild. I think I can solve it by retrying if BBAgent is calling UpdateBuild with final build (which is the most important one). Does that SGTU?",
      "parentUuid": "9f5bdc12_868f4b3e",
      "revId": "93b90e3f224835ca4e5efcc18bc10edd0fd4a943",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": false,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "8bbe79c2_d31f038f",
        "filename": "/PATCHSET_LEVEL",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 0,
      "author": {
        "id": 1002539
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-11-13T00:58:34Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Yes.\n\nAlso have we considered to allow bbagent itself to move the build from SCHEDULED to STARTED? Why do we have to wait for BB server to update the state?",
      "parentUuid": "a5228a10_0c841c08",
      "revId": "93b90e3f224835ca4e5efcc18bc10edd0fd4a943",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": false,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "4f94dc08_6a7f06a4",
        "filename": "/PATCHSET_LEVEL",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 0,
      "author": {
        "id": 1381059
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-11-13T01:15:29Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "That\u0027s a good point. I\u0027m not sure if this is an intentional design choice. BBAgent can certain update the status. Let me check if anything in BB is blocking that.\n\nI will still make the change to retry on final build since I think it is useful anyway.",
      "parentUuid": "8bbe79c2_d31f038f",
      "revId": "93b90e3f224835ca4e5efcc18bc10edd0fd4a943",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba"
    },
